Sentencas: This work investigates the activation and delamination of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-delta (LSCF) air electrode of solid oxide electrolyzer cells sintered on yttria-stabilized zirconia (YSZ) electrolyte.
Titulo: Activation and failure mechanism of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe08O3-δ air electrode in solid oxide electrolyzer cells under high-current electrolysis

Sentencas: After polarization with an electrolysis current of 1 A cm(-2) for 24 h at 800 degrees C, the LSCF electrode delaminates accompanied by an increase of ohmic and polarization resistance.
Titulo: Activation and failure mechanism of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe08O3-δ air electrode in solid oxide electrolyzer cells under high-current electrolysis

Sentencas: Notably, polarization resistance decreases at the beginning.
Titulo: Activation and failure mechanism of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe08O3-δ air electrode in solid oxide electrolyzer cells under high-current electrolysis

Sentencas: By scanning electron microscopy (SEM), a thin but dense layer is observed at the LSCF YSZ interface of an as prepared sample, which is identified as SrZrO3 phase by X-ray diffractometry.
Titulo: Activation and failure mechanism of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe08O3-δ air electrode in solid oxide electrolyzer cells under high-current electrolysis

Sentencas: This layer causes the initial high polarization resistance due to retarded ionic and electronic conductivity.
Titulo: Activation and failure mechanism of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe08O3-δ air electrode in solid oxide electrolyzer cells under high-current electrolysis

Sentencas: After the test, SEM reveals that the SrZrO3 layer delaminates from YSZ electrolyte.
Titulo: Activation and failure mechanism of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe08O3-δ air electrode in solid oxide electrolyzer cells under high-current electrolysis

Sentencas: Moreover, energy dispersive X-ray tests confirm that Co diffuses to the SrZrO3 layer and SrZrO3 YSZ interface.
Titulo: Activation and failure mechanism of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe08O3-δ air electrode in solid oxide electrolyzer cells under high-current electrolysis

Sentencas: Later, the LSCF electrode with Co-containing SrZrO3 layer is shown to perform better than that with pure SrZrO3 layer.
Titulo: Activation and failure mechanism of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe08O3-δ air electrode in solid oxide electrolyzer cells under high-current electrolysis

Sentencas: Thus, Co diffusion can be the reason for the initial decrease of polarization resistance and renders the generation of oxygen at SrZrO3-YSZ interface during the electrolysis.
Titulo: Activation and failure mechanism of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe08O3-δ air electrode in solid oxide electrolyzer cells under high-current electrolysis

Sentencas: Owing to its limited porosity, the SrZrO3 layer traps the generated oxygen.
Titulo: Activation and failure mechanism of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe08O3-δ air electrode in solid oxide electrolyzer cells under high-current electrolysis

Sentencas: High pressure eventually builds up at the SrZrO3 YSZ interface driving the delamination of SrZrO3 layer, and hence the entire LSCF electrode.
Titulo: Activation and failure mechanism of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe08O3-δ air electrode in solid oxide electrolyzer cells under high-current electrolysis
